228
00:19:02.438 --> 00:19:04.239
The court orders.

229
00:19:05.323 --> 00:19:07.055
The plaintiffs' claims are...

230
00:19:07.055 --> 00:19:08.988
dismissed.

231
00:19:28.893 --> 00:19:30.908
What does that mean?

232
00:19:30.908 --> 00:19:33.178
Dismissed means what. exactly?

233
00:19:33.178 --> 00:19:35.995
Not just no wrongdoing.

234
00:19:35.995 --> 00:19:38.296
but no crime.

235
00:19:38.981 --> 00:19:42.229
- Not guilty.
- What did you say?

236
00:19:42.229 --> 00:19:44.447
Not guilty?

237
00:19:45.302 --> 00:19:48.068
How can they be not guilty?

238
00:19:48.655 --> 00:19:50.801
My child worked there

239
00:19:50.801 --> 00:19:52.691
and came down with a deadly illness.

240
00:19:52.691 --> 00:19:54.938
How is the owner not guilty?

241
00:19:54.938 --> 00:19:56.429
How is he innocent?

242
00:19:56.429 --> 00:19:58.760
How is he...

243
00:19:58.760 --> 00:20:02.214
What kind of heartless law is this?

244
00:20:02.214 --> 00:20:05.263
How are we supposed to live
with this injustice?

245
00:20:05.263 --> 00:20:08.590
I can't live with this.

246
00:20:12.540 --> 00:20:13.858
My goodness.

247
00:20:13.858 --> 00:20:15.369
Oh. no.

248
00:20:15.369 --> 00:20:16.437
Hey.

249
00:20:16.437 --> 00:20:18.199
Na Young.

250
00:20:18.199 --> 00:20:19.887
You're bleeding.

251
00:20:19.887 --> 00:20:21.457
What do we do?

252
00:20:21.457 --> 00:20:23.466
What do we do...

253
00:20:25.162 --> 00:20:27.434
Grandma...

254
00:20:27.434 --> 00:20:30.167
I'm so sorry.

255
00:20:31.094 --> 00:20:33.927
Oh. my child.

256
00:20:33.927 --> 00:20:35.012
Na Young.

257
00:20:35.012 --> 00:20:37.547
My poor child...

258
00:20:38.541 --> 00:20:42.494
What are we supposed to do...

259
00:20:47.795 --> 00:20:50.264
My child...

260
00:20:50.264 --> 00:20:53.876
My poor child.

261
00:21:08.466 --> 00:21:11.143
<i>I heard you had it dismissed.</i>

262
00:21:12.437 --> 00:21:15.111
Why did you do something
I never told you to?

263
00:21:15.111 --> 00:21:17.449
Why?

264
00:21:17.449 --> 00:21:20.314
<i>Just do what you're paid for!</i>

265
00:21:20.314 --> 00:21:21.693
<i>You think they'll be grateful</i>

266
00:21:21.693 --> 00:21:24.295
if you give them more than that?

267
00:21:24.295 --> 00:21:27.534
They'll just try to cut the fee.

268
00:21:27.534 --> 00:21:29.544
I'll be careful.

269
00:21:57.874 --> 00:22:00.431
He definitely cut a backroom deal
with Gojin Chemical.

270
00:22:00.431 --> 00:22:03.871
He's got nothing. yet he's greedy as hell.

271
00:22:03.871 --> 00:22:07.049
Even a lapdog needs ambition to be useful.

272
00:22:07.049 --> 00:22:08.754
If he has no greed at all.

273
00:22:08.754 --> 00:22:11.427
what would you use him for?

274
00:22:57.756 --> 00:23:01.242
I'm Joo Young Ho. I'm in second grade.

275
00:23:01.242 --> 00:23:03.376
Is this for me?

276
00:23:07.581 --> 00:23:08.749
Yeah.

277
00:23:08.749 --> 00:23:10.675
Thanks.

278
00:23:11.635 --> 00:23:14.539
I won first place in the race at our school.

279
00:23:14.539 --> 00:23:17.007
Wow. that's awesome.

280
00:23:17.912 --> 00:23:19.955
Thank you.

281
00:23:20.986 --> 00:23:23.852
So... are you a runner?

282
00:23:23.852 --> 00:23:25.825
No.

283
00:23:29.144 --> 00:23:31.900
Then why are you running so hard...

284
00:23:31.900 --> 00:23:34.847
if you're not an athlete?

285
00:23:37.175 --> 00:23:39.018
Pardon?

286
00:23:57.945 --> 00:23:59.500
[Judge Lee Han Young Clears
Responsibility in Nine Deaths]

287
00:24:02.563 --> 00:24:05.368
<i>A 25-year-old woman battling leukemia</i>

288
00:24:05.368 --> 00:24:08.976
<i>had been waiting for legal relief
as a victim of an industrial accident.</i>

289
00:24:08.976 --> 00:24:11.687
<i>But the court ruled there was
insufficient proof of causation</i>

290
00:24:11.687 --> 00:24:13.638
<i>and did not hold the company liable.</i>

291
00:24:13.638 --> 00:24:15.524
<i>That afternoon. she took her own life</i>

292
00:24:15.524 --> 00:24:17.484
<i>from the rooftop of a hospital.</i>

293
00:24:17.484 --> 00:24:19.361
<i>This is Choi Ha Young reporting.</i>

294
00:24:19.361 --> 00:24:22.072
<i>In hospital security footage in Seoul.</i>

295
00:24:22.072 --> 00:24:24.503
<i>a woman in a wheelchair is
seen heading somewhere.</i>

296
00:24:24.503 --> 00:24:27.161
<i>She is the late Han Na Young.
who developed leukemia</i>

297
00:24:27.161 --> 00:24:29.892
<i>while working at Gojin Chemical's Yeoju plant.</i>

298
00:24:29.892 --> 00:24:31.123
<i>Earlier that day.</i>

299
00:24:31.123 --> 00:24:34.148
<i>the Seoul High Court ruled
that Gojin Chemical was not responsible.</i>

300
00:24:34.148 --> 00:24:35.169
<i>Hours later.</i>

301
00:24:35.169 --> 00:24:37.780
<i>she jumped from the hospital rooftop.</i>

302
00:24:37.780 --> 00:24:39.278
<i>Her note says.</i>

303
00:24:39.278 --> 00:24:41.615
<i>"I don't want to be a burden
to my grandma...</i>

304
00:24:41.615 --> 00:24:43.753
<i>who collects scrap anymore."</i>

305
00:24:43.753 --> 00:24:46.064
<i>Short but filled with despair.</i>

306
00:24:46.064 --> 00:24:47.742
<i>the message shows</i>

307
00:24:47.742 --> 00:24:51.060
<i>how long she had been waiting
for justice under the law.</i>

308
00:24:51.060 --> 00:24:53.368
<i>Nine people are dead.
and they walk free?</i>

309
00:24:53.368 --> 00:24:54.853
<i>Is this justice. Your Honor?</i>

310
00:24:54.853 --> 00:24:57.149
<i>People driven to desperate deaths...</i>

311
00:24:57.149 --> 00:24:58.525
<i>The law turns its back again.</i>

312
00:24:58.525 --> 00:25:01.320
<i>Judge Lee Han Young.
does death mean so little to you?</i>

313
00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:03.864
<i>A world where victims die
and perpetrators are protected.</i>

314
00:25:03.864 --> 00:25:06.213
<i>Truly heartbreaking.</i>

315
00:25:24.394 --> 00:25:26.612
<i>Then why are you running so hard...</i>

316
00:25:26.612 --> 00:25:29.280
<i>if you're not an athlete?</i>

317
00:25:29.280 --> 00:25:31.247
Yeah...

318
00:25:32.180 --> 00:25:34.772
I really don't know anymore.

319
00:26:24.738 --> 00:26:27.574
The additional cost is
three hundred million in bearer bonds.

320
00:26:27.574 --> 00:26:29.491
Is this really appropriate for a judge?

321
00:26:29.491 --> 00:26:32.984
That's exactly why I can do this.

322
00:26:40.214 --> 00:26:42.369
Isn't today your mom's birthday?

323
00:26:42.369 --> 00:26:43.937
She called earlier.

324
00:26:43.937 --> 00:26:48.133
I wondered what was going on.
She never calls.

325
00:26:48.133 --> 00:26:50.239
Come over here.

326
00:26:52.320 --> 00:26:55.021
She asked how you were.

327
00:26:55.021 --> 00:26:58.002
I guess she wants a birthday call from you.

328
00:26:58.002 --> 00:27:01.195
She could've called you about that.

329
00:27:01.931 --> 00:27:03.643
She can't even call her own son.

330
00:27:03.643 --> 00:27:06.131
so why does she want congratulations?

331
00:27:07.554 --> 00:27:08.850
I was going to send this...

332
00:27:08.850 --> 00:27:10.675
Do you really...

333
00:27:10.675 --> 00:27:13.769
think this suits my mother?

334
00:27:16.606 --> 00:27:19.683
[Yoo Se Hee.
Youngest Daughter of Haenal Law Firm]

335
00:27:19.940 --> 00:27:22.527
I don't know.

336
00:27:22.527 --> 00:27:25.720
Do I really have to think about all that?

337
00:27:26.643 --> 00:27:30.302
The receipt's inside. so whatever.

338
00:27:30.302 --> 00:27:33.581
If she doesn't like it.
she can exchange it or take the cash.

339
00:27:33.581 --> 00:27:36.256
Tell her to do whatever she wants.

340
00:27:36.256 --> 00:27:39.483
Either way. I did my duty as a daughter-in-law.

341
00:27:53.627 --> 00:27:55.873
Yeah. I know.

342
00:27:55.873 --> 00:27:57.786
When it comes to being
a daughter-in-law in name only.

343
00:27:57.786 --> 00:27:59.872
you're the best.

344
00:28:53.485 --> 00:28:55.371
<i>No!</i>

345
00:29:00.167 --> 00:29:02.540
<i>Father!</i>

346
00:29:04.405 --> 00:29:07.664
Did my father recognize me?

347
00:29:18.192 --> 00:29:20.215
Mother.

348
00:29:20.215 --> 00:29:22.951
Happy birthday.

349
00:29:26.977 --> 00:29:28.695
I wondered why...

350
00:29:28.695 --> 00:29:30.988
my birthday had to fall on a day like today.

351
00:29:30.988 --> 00:29:33.801
Maybe it's because you were meant to come.

352
00:29:41.054 --> 00:29:43.334
I'm glad you're here.

353
00:29:43.974 --> 00:29:46.224
If you hadn't come.

354
00:29:46.224 --> 00:29:48.750
I would've gone to you.

355
00:29:51.634 --> 00:29:53.987
Of course I came. It's your birthday.

356
00:29:53.987 --> 00:29:56.373
But where are you going?

357
00:30:18.590 --> 00:30:21.784
The granddaughter downstairs took her own life.

358
00:30:22.915 --> 00:30:26.702
They say she vomited blood in court yesterday.

359
00:30:27.437 --> 00:30:29.879
People are saying...

360
00:30:29.879 --> 00:30:32.445
some damn judge...

361
00:30:32.445 --> 00:30:36.051
pushed a dying person over the edge.

362
00:30:39.223 --> 00:30:43.743
You know exactly who that damn judge is. Right?

363
00:30:43.743 --> 00:30:45.333
Let's go.

364
00:30:45.333 --> 00:30:47.270
We should...

365
00:30:47.270 --> 00:30:50.163
at least apologize to the living.

366
00:30:51.354 --> 00:30:53.505
No.

367
00:30:53.505 --> 00:30:55.173
I ruled according to the law.

368
00:30:55.173 --> 00:30:56.831
So...

369
00:30:56.831 --> 00:30:59.431
I have nothing to apologize for.

370
00:31:00.772 --> 00:31:02.382
You shouldn't go either.

371
00:31:02.382 --> 00:31:03.617
Why?

372
00:31:03.617 --> 00:31:06.601
Afraid I'll get grabbed by the hair
for being that your mom?

373
00:31:06.601 --> 00:31:09.398
You could get hurt for no reason.

374
00:31:09.398 --> 00:31:11.401
- Please don't go.
- You...

375
00:31:11.401 --> 00:31:14.179
Did you really judge that case fairly?

376
00:31:14.179 --> 00:31:15.980
Yes.

377
00:31:20.007 --> 00:31:22.154
Well...

378
00:31:22.154 --> 00:31:23.722
This isn't something you figure out

379
00:31:23.722 --> 00:31:25.740
by arguing it out.

380
00:31:25.740 --> 00:31:28.466
If you're human. you just know.

381
00:31:30.241 --> 00:31:32.126
Still...

382
00:31:34.958 --> 00:31:37.879
if you were truly fair.

383
00:31:37.879 --> 00:31:40.115
look me in the eye and say it again.

384
00:31:40.115 --> 00:31:42.078
Like. "Mom."

385
00:31:42.078 --> 00:31:44.021
"I judged the case fairly."

386
00:31:44.021 --> 00:31:45.715
"I am a fair judge."

387
00:31:45.715 --> 00:31:46.907
Then I'll believe you

388
00:31:46.907 --> 00:31:49.801
and stand by you no matter what.

389
00:31:49.801 --> 00:31:52.328
"My son is not some damn judge."

390
00:31:52.328 --> 00:31:54.981
"He's an upright judge. fair under heaven."

391
00:31:54.981 --> 00:31:56.932
So if anyone dares badmouth my son.

392
00:31:56.932 --> 00:31:59.702
I won't let it slide.

393
00:32:11.285 --> 00:32:14.365
How did my son end up like this?

394
00:32:14.365 --> 00:32:16.667
Mom...

395
00:32:21.412 --> 00:32:24.373
If my child did something wrong.

396
00:32:24.373 --> 00:32:27.530
then as his mother.
I should be the one to answer for it.

397
00:32:27.530 --> 00:32:29.331
Mom...

398
00:33:05.845 --> 00:33:09.278
Welcome. my dear Chief Justice.

399
00:33:09.278 --> 00:33:11.225
Please come in.

400
00:33:16.187 --> 00:33:16.632
[Kang Shin Jin. Chief Justice]

401
00:33:16.658 --> 00:33:20.433
That crazy witch. Kim Jin Ah
[Kang Shin Jin. Chief Justice]

402
00:33:20.433 --> 00:33:23.472
cleaned out S Group's coffers.

403
00:33:25.763 --> 00:33:28.062
I'll take care of it.

404
00:33:28.062 --> 00:33:29.912
It won't be free. Right?

405
00:33:29.912 --> 00:33:33.242
Isn't this costing more than it's worth?

406
00:33:33.242 --> 00:33:35.848
You said it was the group's coffers.

407
00:33:42.291 --> 00:33:44.697
Alright. I get it.

408
00:33:51.386 --> 00:33:52.912
This is Kang Shin Jin.

409
00:33:52.912 --> 00:33:55.259
<i>Hello. Chief Justice.</i>

410
00:33:55.259 --> 00:33:58.025
You know S Group is in trouble.

411
00:33:58.025 --> 00:34:00.149
What about Judge Lee Han Young?

412
00:34:00.149 --> 00:34:02.669
If you assign the case to him.

413
00:34:02.669 --> 00:34:04.825
he is perfect.

414
00:34:05.705 --> 00:34:07.773
We'll remove anything

415
00:34:07.773 --> 00:34:10.258
that could interfere with the trial.

416
00:34:10.258 --> 00:34:12.318
I'll hang up now.

417
00:34:14.704 --> 00:34:16.272
Who is Lee Han Young?

418
00:34:16.272 --> 00:34:17.678
He's a judge.

419
00:34:17.678 --> 00:34:21.171
Haenal Law Firm brought him in
as a son-in-law lapdog.

420
00:34:22.065 --> 00:34:23.847
So...

421
00:34:23.847 --> 00:34:27.961
he rules however his masters tell him to?

422
00:34:28.636 --> 00:34:31.417
A lapdog does what he's told.

423
00:34:51.501 --> 00:34:52.885
[Yoo Seon Cheol]

424
00:34:53.089 --> 00:34:54.890
Hello?

425
00:34:56.509 --> 00:34:58.310
Now?

426
00:35:05.772 --> 00:35:08.045
Yes. understood.

427
00:35:30.957 --> 00:35:33.083
Hello.

428
00:35:33.083 --> 00:35:35.008
He is Judge Lee Han Young.

429
00:35:35.008 --> 00:35:36.795
assigned to the S Group case.

430
00:35:36.795 --> 00:35:38.123
Oh.

431
00:35:38.123 --> 00:35:40.620
I look forward to working with you.

432
00:35:41.253 --> 00:35:44.726
He is Chairman Jang Tae Sik of S Group.

433
00:35:47.800 --> 00:35:50.099
Nice to meet you.

434
00:36:27.408 --> 00:36:31.771
So your son is hiding somewhere.
and you are here instead?

435
00:36:31.771 --> 00:36:35.842
If you had any guts.
you'd drag that damn judge here.

436
00:36:35.842 --> 00:36:38.591
Why did you come here alone?

437
00:36:38.591 --> 00:36:40.576
I'm sorry.

438
00:36:40.576 --> 00:36:42.941
Sorry for what?

439
00:36:42.941 --> 00:36:44.468
If you're really sorry.

440
00:36:44.468 --> 00:36:47.163
bring your son who handed down

441
00:36:47.163 --> 00:36:51.225
that acquittal. that dismissal.

442
00:36:51.225 --> 00:36:55.028
and cut my granddaughter's life short.

443
00:36:56.953 --> 00:36:58.999
I'm sorry.

444
00:37:03.826 --> 00:37:04.859
Bring my...

445
00:37:04.859 --> 00:37:07.224
- I'm sorry.
- Bring my child back!

446
00:37:07.224 --> 00:37:08.495
My poor child...

447
00:37:08.495 --> 00:37:10.663
I'm so sorry.

448
00:37:12.189 --> 00:37:15.978
Bring her back!

449
00:37:18.577 --> 00:37:21.803
Among the documents the prosecution seized.

450
00:37:21.803 --> 00:37:25.835
there's the embezzlement of
S Construction's funds. correct?

451
00:37:26.996 --> 00:37:29.009
Embezzlement?

452
00:37:29.009 --> 00:37:31.577
No. that money is all mine.

453
00:37:35.243 --> 00:37:37.189
There are also documents showing slush funds

454
00:37:37.189 --> 00:37:40.462
created using embezzled company money.

455
00:37:44.401 --> 00:37:46.368
So?

456
00:37:47.047 --> 00:37:50.808
Slush funds and embezzlement...

457
00:37:51.934 --> 00:37:55.756
If the head of S Construction
takes the fall for both.

458
00:37:55.756 --> 00:37:58.155
there won't be a problem.

459
00:38:07.347 --> 00:38:10.858
So that's what needs to be removed.

460
00:38:58.644 --> 00:39:01.238
Pour him a drink.

461
00:39:04.155 --> 00:39:05.956
Okay.

462
00:39:07.377 --> 00:39:11.604
Is it okay for a judge to pour me a drink?

463
00:39:15.138 --> 00:39:16.831
In this room. he is not a judge.

464
00:39:16.831 --> 00:39:19.839
He is with Haenal Law Firm.

465
00:39:21.882 --> 00:39:23.767
Yeah.

466
00:39:28.521 --> 00:39:30.440
Here.

467
00:39:31.558 --> 00:39:33.526
Hey.

468
00:41:10.745 --> 00:41:12.118
Sir. cardiac arrest!

469
00:41:12.118 --> 00:41:14.583
- Starting CPR now!
- Okay.

470
00:41:14.583 --> 00:41:18.624
Yeah. it's ready.

471
00:41:42.461 --> 00:41:46.212
[Supreme Court]

472
00:41:46.236 --> 00:41:47.664
Make sure the S Group case...

473
00:41:47.664 --> 00:41:50.452
gets assigned to Judge Lee Han Young.

474
00:41:50.452 --> 00:41:52.319
Things are a bit noisy right now.

475
00:41:52.319 --> 00:41:54.353
with the Gojin Chemical victim's death.

476
00:41:54.353 --> 00:41:57.221
Also. he's on leave after his mother passed.
[Kim Jin Han. Justice]

477
00:41:57.221 --> 00:41:58.622
Once he's back.

478
00:41:58.622 --> 00:42:00.238
we'll transfer him to Criminal Division

479
00:42:00.238 --> 00:42:01.768
and finalize the assignment.

480
00:42:01.768 --> 00:42:03.537
What about the head of S Construction?

481
00:42:03.537 --> 00:42:06.771
It'll be taken care of tomorrow.

482
00:42:06.771 --> 00:42:08.885
Okay.

483
00:42:09.777 --> 00:42:11.783
Public fund embezzlement.
and slush fund records...

484
00:42:11.783 --> 00:42:13.929
it's all in here.

485
00:42:17.533 --> 00:42:20.160
Illegal loans from financial institutions.

486
00:42:20.160 --> 00:42:22.503
and bribery charges too.

487
00:42:25.455 --> 00:42:27.040
If you take all of this alone.

488
00:42:27.040 --> 00:42:29.815
you'll be making your own coffin in prison.

489
00:42:32.421 --> 00:42:33.766
If you keep holding out.

490
00:42:33.766 --> 00:42:36.894
do you think Chairman will send you a lifeline?

491
00:42:37.680 --> 00:42:39.898
I doubt it.

492
00:42:40.864 --> 00:42:43.322
He's probably deciding right now

493
00:42:43.322 --> 00:42:46.420
whether to send down a coffin made of paulownia

494
00:42:46.420 --> 00:42:48.812
or one made of cedar.

495
00:43:01.081 --> 00:43:03.547
You should think about your family.

496
00:43:13.502 --> 00:43:15.108
Deputy Chief.

497
00:43:15.108 --> 00:43:16.713
What is it now?

498
00:43:16.713 --> 00:43:18.138
Presiding Judge Lee Han Young

499
00:43:18.138 --> 00:43:19.933
is transferring to the Criminal Division.

500
00:43:19.933 --> 00:43:21.084
What?

501
00:43:21.084 --> 00:43:22.183
Who?

502
00:43:22.183 --> 00:43:24.643
You haven't heard about him?

503
00:43:25.675 --> 00:43:29.437
Looks like S group pulled some strings.

504
00:43:30.615 --> 00:43:32.416
Really?

505
00:43:33.193 --> 00:43:35.186
Dig into it. Now.

506
00:43:35.186 --> 00:43:36.987
Yes.

507
00:43:46.123 --> 00:43:48.007
Have some.

508
00:43:49.232 --> 00:43:51.336
Please.

509
00:43:53.215 --> 00:43:55.274
It'll get cold.

510
00:44:02.100 --> 00:44:04.867
You don't need to worry about your family.

511
00:44:06.420 --> 00:44:09.429
I'm just saying it'll be harder if you refuse.

512
00:44:12.840 --> 00:44:14.784
In detention.

513
00:44:14.784 --> 00:44:16.877
Not here.

514
00:44:22.608 --> 00:44:24.808
Hello. sir.

515
00:44:27.437 --> 00:44:29.102
So you start at the Criminal Division

516
00:44:29.102 --> 00:44:32.429
of the Seoul Central District Court tomorrow?

517
00:44:32.429 --> 00:44:33.621
Yeah. right.

518
00:44:33.621 --> 00:44:35.422
All right.

519
00:44:38.581 --> 00:44:39.983
Come to think of it.

520
00:44:39.983 --> 00:44:42.661
Yoo Seon Cheol of Haenal Law Firm

521
00:44:42.661 --> 00:44:45.547
seems to care about you quite a lot.

522
00:44:54.560 --> 00:44:57.273
He's from a regional university.
and his training ranking was average.

523
00:44:57.273 --> 00:44:58.905
The year he started handling cases solo.

524
00:44:58.905 --> 00:45:01.025
<i>he married into Haenal Law Firm.</i>

525
00:45:01.025 --> 00:45:02.349
<i>From then on.</i>

526
00:45:02.349 --> 00:45:04.084
a front law firm Haenal set up.

527
00:45:04.084 --> 00:45:08.756
Gwangmin Law Firm.
has a one-hundred-percent win rate.

528
00:45:08.756 --> 00:45:12.354
They were all Judge Lee Han Young's cases.

529
00:45:12.354 --> 00:45:14.404
<i>They didn't gain a son-in-law.</i>

530
00:45:14.404 --> 00:45:16.124
<i>They gained an ally.</i>

531
00:45:16.124 --> 00:45:17.192
That's probably why

532
00:45:17.192 --> 00:45:18.718
he was the first in his class
to make presiding judge.

533
00:45:18.718 --> 00:45:19.911
<i>What a bastard.</i>

534
00:45:19.911 --> 00:45:22.629
But aside from the Gwangmin cases.

535
00:45:22.629 --> 00:45:24.698
his other rulings are considered
fairly balanced.

536
00:45:24.698 --> 00:45:26.600
So not a complete bastard?

537
00:45:26.600 --> 00:45:29.002
Lee Han Young's father has dementia.

538
00:45:29.002 --> 00:45:31.349
He's in a nursing facility in Gwacheon.

539
00:45:31.349 --> 00:45:33.477
<i>Wow...</i>

540
00:45:33.477 --> 00:45:36.117
<i>Do you know how much a year there costs?</i>

541
00:45:36.117 --> 00:45:38.098
Two hundred million won.

542
00:45:38.098 --> 00:45:40.125
The payments are from Yoo Se Hee.

543
00:45:40.125 --> 00:45:42.269
It's Lee Han Young's wife.

544
00:45:42.269 --> 00:45:46.422
<i>Looks like he benefits plenty from his in-laws.</i>

545
00:45:46.422 --> 00:45:48.804
but there's nothing in his own name.

546
00:45:48.804 --> 00:45:50.823
<i>He must be stashing it somewhere.</i>

547
00:45:50.823 --> 00:45:53.011
Any women? Gambling? Anything else?

548
00:45:53.011 --> 00:45:55.976
He's a judge Haenal Law Firm has on a leash.

549
00:45:55.976 --> 00:45:57.711
We need at least one weakness.

550
00:45:57.711 --> 00:45:59.748
<i>He's got two nicknames.</i>

551
00:45:59.748 --> 00:46:02.573
<i>One is "the in-laws' lapdog."</i>

552
00:46:02.573 --> 00:46:03.730
Ever seen servants get paid

553
00:46:03.730 --> 00:46:07.148
when the masters make deals?

554
00:46:07.148 --> 00:46:10.933
No woman trouble. No gambling either.

555
00:46:10.933 --> 00:46:12.424
Among bastards.

556
00:46:12.424 --> 00:46:14.639
he's the obedient kind.

557
00:46:16.773 --> 00:46:18.195
Anything else?

558
00:46:18.195 --> 00:46:19.596
You said two nicknames.

559
00:46:19.596 --> 00:46:20.927
Six-dot.

560
00:46:20.927 --> 00:46:22.078
"Six-dot?"

561
00:46:22.078 --> 00:46:23.791
Sounds like gambling.

562
00:46:23.791 --> 00:46:25.970
No. he doesn't gamble.

563
00:46:25.970 --> 00:46:29.404
It's because he clocks out at six. sharp.

564
00:46:37.829 --> 00:46:40.504
Is that even possible for a Korean judge?

565
00:46:40.504 --> 00:46:43.090
<i>Yes. He's Haenal's son-in-law.</i>

566
00:46:43.090 --> 00:46:44.801
<i>That's why his caseload is...</i>

567
00:46:44.801 --> 00:46:46.101
<i>kept reasonable.</i>

568
00:46:46.101 --> 00:46:48.598
<i>Looks like you'll have to find
his weakness yourself. sir.</i>

569
00:46:48.598 --> 00:46:50.698
Hang up.

570
00:47:32.330 --> 00:47:34.855
Hey. Number 522!

571
00:47:34.855 --> 00:47:36.656
Wake up!

572
00:47:37.708 --> 00:47:39.938
What?

573
00:47:39.938 --> 00:47:42.524
How the hell...

574
00:47:42.524 --> 00:47:44.401
did you botch the surveillance?

575
00:47:44.401 --> 00:47:45.430
<i>What do we do?</i>

576
00:47:45.430 --> 00:47:48.438
<i>If this gets out.
they'll scream coercive investigation.</i>

577
00:47:48.438 --> 00:47:50.632
<i>Should we slap an embargo
on the legal reporters first?</i>

578
00:47:50.632 --> 00:47:52.527
No.

579
00:47:52.527 --> 00:47:54.684
Leak it as a tip from a prosecution source.

580
00:47:54.684 --> 00:47:57.503
that homicide is a possibility.

581
00:47:57.503 --> 00:48:01.250
Then one of them will come
begging to save themselves.

582
00:48:23.547 --> 00:48:26.300
[50 million won]

583
00:48:47.199 --> 00:48:49.167
Han Young?

584
00:48:50.463 --> 00:48:52.497
My dear son.

585
00:48:52.497 --> 00:48:54.991
You have to be a judge.

586
00:49:02.176 --> 00:49:04.147
I became a judge a long time ago.

587
00:49:04.147 --> 00:49:07.094
Why are you still saying that?

588
00:49:07.094 --> 00:49:10.767
I don't even know
if I became a judge the way you wanted.

589
00:49:10.767 --> 00:49:13.902
Your son is so kind.

590
00:49:15.726 --> 00:49:18.477
You're Judge Lee Han Young. right?

591
00:49:18.477 --> 00:49:19.862
I'm Prosecutor Kim Jin Ah...

592
00:49:19.862 --> 00:49:22.850
from the Special Division
of the Seoul Central Prosecutors' Office.

593
00:49:27.270 --> 00:49:29.415
We'll be seeing each other in court soon.

594
00:49:29.415 --> 00:49:32.736
You know. Chairman Jang Tae Sik of S Group...

595
00:49:32.736 --> 00:49:35.037
I'll be indicting him.

596
00:49:35.952 --> 00:49:38.517
I stirred up S Group's reservoir.

597
00:49:38.517 --> 00:49:41.328
and it looks like people up top panicked.

598
00:49:41.328 --> 00:49:44.105
They even pulled a judge from
the High Court's civil division

599
00:49:44.105 --> 00:49:46.931
into the criminal division.

600
00:49:50.995 --> 00:49:53.493
Fine. You can play dumb.

601
00:49:53.493 --> 00:49:55.661
But this time. let's do it by the book.

602
00:49:55.661 --> 00:49:59.448
Otherwise. I'll start with you
and tear everything apart.

603
00:49:59.448 --> 00:50:01.997
I graduated second in my class
at Hankuk University Law School.

604
00:50:01.997 --> 00:50:05.800
I'm smart. and I've got a very nasty temper.

605
00:50:05.800 --> 00:50:08.750
From what I see. you don't look that smart.

606
00:50:11.829 --> 00:50:15.136
Then I guess you admit the nasty temper part.

607
00:50:17.590 --> 00:50:20.349
If you want to keep living
as your in-laws' lapdog.

608
00:50:20.349 --> 00:50:22.945
let's do it by the book this time.

609
00:50:22.945 --> 00:50:27.031
I'll request full transcripts
and audio recordings at trial.

610
00:50:27.031 --> 00:50:29.668
Don't. I'll deny it.

611
00:50:29.668 --> 00:50:31.156
Why?

612
00:50:31.156 --> 00:50:33.385
Nervous?

613
00:50:34.261 --> 00:50:37.068
If you're nervous. you've already lost.

614
00:50:54.132 --> 00:50:55.300
<i>Breaking news.</i>

615
00:50:55.300 --> 00:50:58.558
<i>Choi Jong Hak. CEO of S Construction.
who was under investigation.</i>

616
00:50:58.558 --> 00:51:00.680
<i>was found unconscious this morning</i>

617
00:51:00.680 --> 00:51:02.805
<i>while in custody at the Seoul Detention Center.</i>

618
00:51:02.805 --> 00:51:05.560
<i>He was rushed to the hospital</i>

619
00:51:05.560 --> 00:51:07.702
<i>but was later pronounced dead.</i>

620
00:51:07.702 --> 00:51:10.013
<i>Police are currently investigating the case.</i>

621
00:51:10.013 --> 00:51:12.451
<i>with suicide considered
the leading possibility.</i>

622
00:51:12.451 --> 00:51:15.862
<i>Given that Choi was a key figure
in the prosecution's investigation...</i>

623
00:51:15.862 --> 00:51:17.280
<i>CEO Choi Jong Hak...</i>

624
00:51:17.280 --> 00:51:18.782
<i>didn't kill himself.</i>

625
00:51:18.782 --> 00:51:20.520
<i>There is growing speculation about</i>

626
00:51:20.520 --> 00:51:22.911
<i>outside pressure or
possible third-party involvement.</i>

627
00:51:22.911 --> 00:51:25.609
<i>Prosecutors have seized
internal off-the-books ledgers.</i>

628
00:51:25.609 --> 00:51:28.795
<i>revealing illegal fund flows
worth trillions of won...</i>

629
00:51:29.575 --> 00:51:31.364
<i>Did you get anything out of him?</i>

630
00:51:31.364 --> 00:51:32.596
No.

631
00:51:32.596 --> 00:51:34.789
I just warned him.

632
00:51:34.789 --> 00:51:36.904
Didn't seem to work.

633
00:51:36.904 --> 00:51:39.344
You should've at least blown up at him.

634
00:51:39.344 --> 00:51:40.929
Yeah.

635
00:51:40.929 --> 00:51:43.349
I'm already regretting it.

636
00:52:19.332 --> 00:52:20.379
Sir.

637
00:52:20.379 --> 00:52:22.429
can we expect a fair trial today?

638
00:52:22.429 --> 00:52:24.327
Will the death of the S Construction CEO

639
00:52:24.327 --> 00:52:26.759
affect the ruling?

640
00:52:28.097 --> 00:52:29.374
Sir.

641
00:52:29.374 --> 00:52:32.067
just one comment please...

642
00:52:34.931 --> 00:52:36.024
Please step back.

643
00:52:36.024 --> 00:52:38.595
Please. sir.

644
00:52:38.595 --> 00:52:40.479
The prosecution is targeting

645
00:52:40.479 --> 00:52:42.053
Chairman Jang Tae Sik of S Group

646
00:52:42.053 --> 00:52:45.368
over embezzlement. slush funds.
and improper lobbying with banks.

647
00:52:45.368 --> 00:52:47.159
The court will rule fairly.

648
00:52:47.159 --> 00:52:48.580
based on the law and the facts.

649
00:52:48.580 --> 00:52:50.920
Please step back.

650
00:52:56.923 --> 00:52:58.882
Just one word. sir.

651
00:53:00.680 --> 00:53:02.920
Hello. Justice.

652
00:53:07.211 --> 00:53:09.189
You were appointed the same time as him?

653
00:53:09.189 --> 00:53:10.060
[Kim Yun Hyeok. Presiding Judge]

654
00:53:10.060 --> 00:53:11.945
Yes.
[Kim Yun Hyeok. Presiding Judge]

655
00:53:13.225 --> 00:53:15.338
Are you two close?

656
00:53:17.228 --> 00:53:20.291
We're on decent terms.

657
00:53:22.155 --> 00:53:24.221
Good.

658
00:53:26.849 --> 00:53:28.214
Aren't you curious...

659
00:53:28.214 --> 00:53:30.192
who killed the S Construction CEO?

660
00:53:30.192 --> 00:53:31.700
It was because of
prosecutorial coercion. right?

661
00:53:31.700 --> 00:53:34.165
Some say he was driven to suicide.

662
00:53:34.165 --> 00:53:36.811
Then you should be out catching the killer.

663
00:53:37.652 --> 00:53:39.220
What's the point?

664
00:53:39.220 --> 00:53:42.609
The court can just acquit him anyway.

665
00:53:42.609 --> 00:53:45.386
As long as you follow the law.

666
00:53:45.386 --> 00:53:48.693
I'd beg on my knees if I had to.

667
00:53:48.693 --> 00:53:51.158
Oh. right.

668
00:53:51.158 --> 00:53:52.726
Not you.

669
00:53:52.726 --> 00:53:55.959
I should do that to Yoo Seon Cheol
at Haenal Law Firm.

670
00:53:56.648 --> 00:53:59.328
Are you out of your mind?

671
00:54:05.586 --> 00:54:06.730
These are the records of...

672
00:54:06.730 --> 00:54:09.550
Chairman Jang Tae Sik's
embezzlement and slush funds.

673
00:54:15.410 --> 00:54:17.022
[Kim Yong Jin.
Accounting Director of S Construction]

674
00:54:18.877 --> 00:54:21.571
They say you're obsessed with
indicting S Group.

675
00:54:21.571 --> 00:54:23.037
Is that a prosecutor's duty.

676
00:54:23.037 --> 00:54:25.990
or a personal grudge?

677
00:54:26.724 --> 00:54:28.670
Both.

678
00:54:30.555 --> 00:54:34.181
I went after Jang Tae Sik
the moment I became a prosecutor.

679
00:54:40.826 --> 00:54:43.199
You have impure motives.

680
00:55:00.509 --> 00:55:02.703
Let's grab lunch.

681
00:55:02.703 --> 00:55:04.662
I'm busy.

682
00:55:07.178 --> 00:55:10.459
This is complicated to handle. isn't it?

683
00:55:12.766 --> 00:55:14.567
Not really.

684
00:55:19.450 --> 00:55:21.804
Anything I can help with?

685
00:55:23.474 --> 00:55:25.527
You'll miss lunch.

686
00:55:25.527 --> 00:55:26.677
What about the ruling?

687
00:55:26.677 --> 00:55:27.911
Yes.

688
00:55:27.911 --> 00:55:30.064
The S Group's trial date is
the day after tomorrow...

689
00:55:30.064 --> 00:55:31.396
So.

690
00:55:31.396 --> 00:55:33.658
the draft ruling should be ready by now.

691
00:55:33.658 --> 00:55:36.815
I'll check it at his lunch.

692
00:55:36.815 --> 00:55:38.775
Okay.

693
00:55:44.472 --> 00:55:46.848
You still here?

694
00:55:49.143 --> 00:55:51.363
I'm heading out now.

695
00:56:05.313 --> 00:56:08.089
He is from a no-name school
with zero connections...

696
00:56:08.089 --> 00:56:11.382
Why did Haenal Law Firm
pick a guy like that?

697
00:56:11.382 --> 00:56:13.848
I'm way better than him.

698
00:56:16.284 --> 00:56:18.978
It looks like the ruling on
Chairman Jang isn't ready yet.

699
00:56:18.978 --> 00:56:21.598
I'm kind of nervous.

700
00:56:38.986 --> 00:56:40.552
Finally...

701
00:56:40.552 --> 00:56:43.293
Are you heading to Haenal Law Firm?

702
00:56:57.856 --> 00:56:59.049
<i>Mr. Yoo.</i>

703
00:56:59.049 --> 00:57:00.927
<i>it's me.</i>

704
00:57:00.927 --> 00:57:03.675
<i>Judge Lee Han Young submitted his resignation.</i>

705
00:57:03.675 --> 00:57:06.057
<i>I thought you should know.</i>

706
00:57:11.414 --> 00:57:12.440
Let's get dinner.

707
00:57:12.440 --> 00:57:14.137
Can't you eat without me?

708
00:57:14.137 --> 00:57:15.975
Not me.

709
00:57:15.975 --> 00:57:18.088
With the Justice.

710
00:57:40.831 --> 00:57:42.715
Thank you.

711
00:57:44.621 --> 00:57:47.092
There's a senior judicial research clerk
at the Supreme Court

712
00:57:47.092 --> 00:57:49.644
whose term is ending soon.

713
00:57:51.016 --> 00:57:54.396
Once that seat opens.
it has to be filled immediately.

714
00:57:55.008 --> 00:57:56.326
That's unfortunate.

715
00:57:56.326 --> 00:57:59.719
If I'd known earlier. I wouldn't have resigned.

716
00:58:01.345 --> 00:58:03.411
You resigned?

717
00:58:04.899 --> 00:58:08.092
After work.
I stopped by the chief judge's office.

718
00:58:12.645 --> 00:58:15.451
Did Yoo Seon Cheol approve it?

719
00:58:18.912 --> 00:58:20.814
Do you really think...

720
00:58:20.814 --> 00:58:23.647
Yoo Seon Cheol approved?

721
00:58:27.136 --> 00:58:28.944
By now.

722
00:58:28.944 --> 00:58:30.255
he probably knows.

723
00:58:30.255 --> 00:58:33.654
Your resignation won't be accepted
for the time being.

724
00:58:35.213 --> 00:58:36.573
Chief Justice Kang Shin Jin

725
00:58:36.573 --> 00:58:39.458
is very interested in this case.

726
00:58:42.047 --> 00:58:45.728
The Supreme Court is bigger than
it looks from the outside.

727
00:58:45.728 --> 00:58:47.341
If you don't like the research post.

728
00:58:47.341 --> 00:58:49.854
decide what you do want.

729
00:58:51.798 --> 00:58:55.071
While you prepare for the S Group trial.

730
00:59:05.646 --> 00:59:08.882
The prosecution will reassign the case
after the first trial.

731
00:59:08.882 --> 00:59:12.698
and a different prosecutor will
handle the appeal.

732
00:59:12.698 --> 00:59:14.317
But...

733
00:59:14.317 --> 00:59:17.048
Judge Lee Han Young is the problem.

734
00:59:17.048 --> 00:59:19.773
He turned down a Supreme Court post...

735
00:59:19.773 --> 00:59:21.874
and resigned.

736
00:59:23.841 --> 00:59:26.726
Did he change that fast?

737
00:59:29.107 --> 00:59:31.576
This is getting messy.

738
00:59:40.286 --> 00:59:42.504
<i>Hello. sir.</i>

739
00:59:43.707 --> 00:59:48.104
Looks like your son-in-law lacks
respect for his father-in-law.

740
00:59:48.104 --> 00:59:50.623
[Haenal Law Firm]

741
00:59:59.006 --> 01:00:01.153
Sit.

742
01:00:10.817 --> 01:00:13.559
Do you only use your mouth in court?

743
01:00:13.559 --> 01:00:17.606
No greeting at all?
Like. "Sir. how have you been?"

744
01:00:18.350 --> 01:00:19.686
Oh.

745
01:00:19.686 --> 01:00:22.652
Is it because I'm younger than you?

746
01:00:27.518 --> 01:00:29.878
Hello. sir.

747
01:00:29.878 --> 01:00:31.292
See? Much nicer.

748
01:00:31.292 --> 01:00:33.890
A family greeting keeps
things nice and friendly.

749
01:00:33.890 --> 01:00:36.132
So. did you resign?

750
01:00:36.947 --> 01:00:38.981
Yes.

751
01:00:38.981 --> 01:00:41.279
Finish the S Group case.

752
01:00:41.279 --> 01:00:42.305
then come back.

753
01:00:42.305 --> 01:00:45.218
No. I'm going independent.

754
01:00:47.244 --> 01:00:50.164
Father. did you hear that?

755
01:00:52.456 --> 01:00:56.369
Did another firm make you an offer?

756
01:00:58.183 --> 01:00:59.918
That'd be interesting.

757
01:00:59.918 --> 01:01:02.842
Haenal's son-in-law working at another firm.

758
01:01:02.842 --> 01:01:04.762
No.

759
01:01:05.851 --> 01:01:08.022
Nothing like that.

760
01:01:09.316 --> 01:01:11.896
We'll talk later.

761
01:01:15.019 --> 01:01:17.565
Presiding Judge Lee Han Young.

762
01:01:18.194 --> 01:01:20.807
This is for you.

763
01:01:25.010 --> 01:01:26.978
What is this?

764
01:01:29.089 --> 01:01:32.029
The final ruling in the S Group case.

765
01:01:36.789 --> 01:01:39.370
<i>A judge's robe represents...</i>

766
01:01:39.370 --> 01:01:41.647
<i>authority entrusted...</i>

767
01:01:41.647 --> 01:01:44.547
<i>by the people.</i>

768
01:01:46.462 --> 01:01:49.514
<i>From now on.</i>

769
01:01:50.830 --> 01:01:54.024
<i>Haenal Law Firm's power</i>

770
01:01:54.024 --> 01:01:56.416
<i>will stand behind that authority.</i>

771
01:02:06.012 --> 01:02:08.953
It's been ten years.

772
01:02:08.953 --> 01:02:11.956
Living like a dog...

773
01:02:11.956 --> 01:02:14.633
on Haenal's leash.

774
01:02:15.541 --> 01:02:17.384
Now...

775
01:02:18.124 --> 01:02:21.529
you're forcing the ruling too?

776
01:02:21.529 --> 01:02:24.095
Finish this case...

777
01:02:24.095 --> 01:02:25.114
and come back.

778
01:02:25.114 --> 01:02:26.324
I'll go independent.

779
01:02:26.324 --> 01:02:28.826
What changes if you're still
Haenal's son-in-law?

780
01:02:28.826 --> 01:02:31.420
Then I'll divorce.

781
01:02:32.681 --> 01:02:33.916
Father.

782
01:02:33.916 --> 01:02:37.727
That's why you don't let
a lapdog taste money.

783
01:02:39.670 --> 01:02:41.594
Lapdog...

784
01:02:41.594 --> 01:02:43.562
Whatever you do.

785
01:02:44.215 --> 01:02:48.001
not until the S Group trial is over.

786
01:02:48.717 --> 01:02:50.913
Understand?

787
01:03:05.333 --> 01:03:08.135
My dealings with Haenal Law Firm

788
01:03:09.487 --> 01:03:11.785
end here.

789
01:03:40.951 --> 01:03:43.551
Should we have a kid?

790
01:03:43.551 --> 01:03:46.547
I'm not saying I'll carry one.

791
01:03:46.547 --> 01:03:48.072
Just bring one from somewhere.

792
01:03:48.072 --> 01:03:50.040
Let's get divorced.

793
01:03:54.004 --> 01:03:56.380
You seeing someone?

794
01:04:03.403 --> 01:04:04.971
Just bring a kid.

795
01:04:04.971 --> 01:04:08.118
If you don't have one. start trying now.

796
01:04:11.286 --> 01:04:14.179
A daughter would be nice.

797
01:04:19.129 --> 01:04:21.852
I told your father.

798
01:04:34.968 --> 01:04:37.521
You can't divorce me.

799
01:04:37.521 --> 01:04:39.661
Divorce happens...

800
01:04:41.872 --> 01:04:45.345
when I decide it does.

801
01:04:48.134 --> 01:04:49.725
Don't come home

802
01:04:49.725 --> 01:04:51.158
until I say...

803
01:04:51.158 --> 01:04:53.558
you can.

804
01:05:21.035 --> 01:05:22.332
<i>Father.</i>

805
01:05:22.332 --> 01:05:25.794
<i>That's why you don't let a lapdog taste money.</i>

806
01:05:26.880 --> 01:05:29.540
I lived like a loser.

807
01:05:35.210 --> 01:05:39.103
You bastard. just drop dead!

808
01:05:41.833 --> 01:05:43.967
What?

809
01:05:43.967 --> 01:05:44.997
Hey.

810
01:05:44.997 --> 01:05:47.303
What did you just say?

811
01:05:47.303 --> 01:05:48.651
What did you just say?

812
01:05:48.651 --> 01:05:50.029
- Don't.
- Let go!

813
01:05:50.029 --> 01:05:52.695
Drop dead. you bastard!

814
01:05:55.819 --> 01:05:58.179
You're nothing.

815
01:05:59.595 --> 01:06:00.653
Hey!

816
01:06:00.653 --> 01:06:02.106
Hey. stop it.

817
01:06:02.106 --> 01:06:03.424
Stop.

818
01:06:03.424 --> 01:06:05.603
Hey. stop it.

819
01:06:05.603 --> 01:06:08.242
Enough. Come here.

820
01:06:08.838 --> 01:06:10.718
Let's just go.

821
01:07:02.381 --> 01:07:04.099
<i>The granddaughter downstairs
took her own life.</i>

822
01:07:04.099 --> 01:07:06.025
<i>The plaintiffs' claims are...</i>

823
01:07:06.025 --> 01:07:08.191
<i>Some damn judge...</i>

824
01:07:08.191 --> 01:07:10.775
<i>- Dismissed.
- pushed a dying person over the edge.</i>

825
01:07:10.775 --> 01:07:12.526
<i>Not guilty?</i>

826
01:07:12.526 --> 01:07:13.778
<i>How is he innocent?</i>

827
01:07:13.778 --> 01:07:15.988
<i>That's why you don't let a lapdog taste money.</i>

828
01:07:15.988 --> 01:07:19.357
<i>What kind of heartless law is this?</i>

829
01:07:19.357 --> 01:07:22.010
<i>How are we supposed to live
with this injustice?</i>

830
01:07:22.010 --> 01:07:24.969
<i>I can't live with this.</i>

831
01:07:41.801 --> 01:07:44.603
<i>How did my son end up like this?</i>

832
01:08:22.718 --> 01:08:25.264
It's time. Why isn't he here yet?

833
01:08:25.264 --> 01:08:28.376
He'll be in any moment.

834
01:08:28.376 --> 01:08:30.695
If the people taking my money worked like this.

835
01:08:30.695 --> 01:08:32.639
they'd all be finished.

836
01:08:32.639 --> 01:08:35.206
Of course. I know.

837
01:08:38.463 --> 01:08:41.348
All rise.

838
01:08:54.772 --> 01:08:57.282
Please be seated.

839
01:09:07.659 --> 01:09:09.394
The defendant. Jang Tae Sik.

840
01:09:09.394 --> 01:09:11.231
is merely a victim of

841
01:09:11.231 --> 01:09:14.324
the reckless and immoral embezzlement
and slush fund schemes

842
01:09:14.324 --> 01:09:17.225
carried out by S Construction
CEO Choi Jong Hak.

843
01:09:17.225 --> 01:09:19.331
However.

844
01:09:19.331 --> 01:09:21.399
an employee's wrongdoing is...

845
01:09:21.399 --> 01:09:25.677
ultimately the chairman's responsibility.

846
01:09:25.677 --> 01:09:28.124
I repent.

847
01:09:37.584 --> 01:09:39.194
For the past ten years.

848
01:09:39.194 --> 01:09:41.680
the defendant used S Construction

849
01:09:41.680 --> 01:09:43.248
as a vehicle for embezzlement

850
01:09:43.248 --> 01:09:46.492
and slush funds.

851
01:09:46.492 --> 01:09:49.358
Also. now seeks to pin his crimes...

852
01:09:49.358 --> 01:09:51.992
on the late CEO Choi Jong Hak.

853
01:09:54.838 --> 01:09:56.814
Accordingly. the prosecution.

854
01:09:56.814 --> 01:10:00.592
under the Act on Aggravated Punishment
of Specific Economic Crimes.

855
01:10:00.592 --> 01:10:03.193
seeks a sentence of...

856
01:10:03.193 --> 01:10:05.300
six years in prison

857
01:10:05.300 --> 01:10:07.444
and a fine of 12 billion won

858
01:10:07.444 --> 01:10:09.859
for the defendant. Jang Tae Sik.

859
01:10:11.747 --> 01:10:13.923
Don't worry.

860
01:10:30.081 --> 01:10:32.848
Defendant. please stand.

861
01:10:59.144 --> 01:11:01.131
The court orders.

862
01:11:02.900 --> 01:11:05.367
The defendant. Jang Tae Sik.

863
01:11:11.762 --> 01:11:14.665
is sentenced to ten years in prison

864
01:11:14.665 --> 01:11:17.037
and a fine of 24 billion won.

865
01:11:17.037 --> 01:11:20.070
The defendant is taken into custody.

866
01:11:22.570 --> 01:11:25.437
What? What just happened?

867
01:11:31.386 --> 01:11:34.415
Did you hear that? Ten years.

868
01:11:34.415 --> 01:11:36.828
Why such a nice ruling?

869
01:11:36.828 --> 01:11:40.025
Is there anyone to notify
of the defendant's detention?

870
01:11:40.025 --> 01:11:41.837
Has he lost his mind?

871
01:11:41.837 --> 01:11:43.610
Hey. come down here!

872
01:11:43.610 --> 01:11:45.090
- What? Detention?
- Please calm down.

873
01:11:45.090 --> 01:11:46.283
Ten years?

874
01:11:46.283 --> 01:11:48.385
Let go of me! Are you kidding me?

875
01:11:48.385 --> 01:11:49.836
Judge Lee!

876
01:11:49.836 --> 01:11:51.461
Redo this!

877
01:11:51.461 --> 01:11:53.367
Hey!

878
01:12:39.515 --> 01:12:42.125
<i>Do you know what you just did?</i>

879
01:12:42.125 --> 01:12:43.272
Tell them to appeal.

880
01:12:43.272 --> 01:12:45.418
<i>What? This punk.</i>

881
01:12:54.276 --> 01:12:56.729
<i>What the hell are you doing?</i>

882
01:13:00.258 --> 01:13:03.117
<i>Ridiculous.</i>

883
01:13:03.117 --> 01:13:05.985
<i>Did you want a divorce that badly?</i>

884
01:13:08.126 --> 01:13:10.678
I'll send the papers.

885
01:13:33.184 --> 01:13:35.881
[Defendant's Seat]

886
01:13:41.091 --> 01:13:43.369
The defendant. Lee Han Young.

887
01:13:43.369 --> 01:13:46.435
is charged with murdering an accomplice

888
01:13:46.435 --> 01:13:48.503
and issuing threats.

889
01:13:48.503 --> 01:13:51.048
The prosecution hereby brings charges

890
01:13:51.048 --> 01:13:53.884
against the defendant. Lee Han Young.

891
01:13:53.884 --> 01:13:55.118
Defendant.

892
01:13:55.118 --> 01:13:57.817
do you admit to the charges?

893
01:14:10.182 --> 01:14:11.625
No. No.

894
01:14:11.625 --> 01:14:13.968
No!

895
01:14:13.968 --> 01:14:16.173
Defendant.

896
01:14:16.173 --> 01:14:18.274
It wasn't me!

897
01:14:23.370 --> 01:14:25.811
No.

898
01:14:25.811 --> 01:14:27.535
I...

899
01:14:27.535 --> 01:14:30.462
I am not guilty.

900
01:14:31.136 --> 01:14:33.749
I'm not guilty!

901
01:14:34.422 --> 01:14:37.334
I'm not guilty.

902
01:14:40.600 --> 01:14:44.413
[The Judge Returns]

903
01:15:05.501 --> 01:15:08.272
[Thank you Kim Dong Jun and Kim Song Il for their special appearance]

904
01:15:08.415 --> 01:15:10.227
<i>I'll prove my own innocence.</i>

905
01:15:10.228 --> 01:15:12.098
<i>You can't handle this alone.</i>

906
01:15:12.098 --> 01:15:13.170
<i>You piece of trash!</i>

907
01:15:13.170 --> 01:15:15.769
<i>This is what happens when trash plays judge!</i>

908
01:15:15.769 --> 01:15:17.155
<i>I finally want to live...</i>

909
01:15:17.155 --> 01:15:20.186
<i>as the real Lee Han Young.</i>

910
01:15:20.186 --> 01:15:21.430
<i>2025?</i>

911
01:15:21.430 --> 01:15:23.799
<i>I'm back exactly ten years.</i>

912
01:15:23.799 --> 01:15:25.214
<i>Kim Sang Jin?</i>

913
01:15:25.214 --> 01:15:27.097
<i>Arrest him now.
If you don't. that child will die.</i>

914
01:15:27.097 --> 01:15:29.121
<i>- How do you know that?
- Didn't you read the case file?</i>

915
01:15:29.121 --> 01:15:30.478
<i>You released him.</i>

916
01:15:30.478 --> 01:15:31.798
<i>I have a child.</i>

917
01:15:31.798 --> 01:15:32.951
<i>Right. I'm a judge.</i>

918
01:15:32.951 --> 01:15:34.888
<i>Then try Kim Sang Jin with me.</i>

919
01:15:34.888 --> 01:15:38.241
<i>I have to prove he's a serial killer.</i>

920
01:15:39.305 --> 01:16:39.633
